<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">New Indication Opportunities for FPC  &#8226; Evaluated multiple potential new indication opportunities for FPC and treatment of iron deficiency   and/or anemia &#8226; FPC as an iron therapeutic has the potential to provide benefit in multiple disease states &#8226; Based on analysis of development considerations, economics and pricing, and regimen ergonomics   (continuous I.V. infusion or multiple bolus doses) &#8211; two leading opportunities have been identified:   &#8226; FPC for home infusion in patients requiring parenteral nutrition    &#8226; Currently iron requirements can only be met with in-office I.V. iron infusion visit (due to hypersensitivity risk),       whereas FPC could be safely administered via an infusion pump at home   &#8226; FPC to improve cardiac function in hospitalized acute congestive heart failure patients    &#8226; Parenteral IONP studies have consistently demonstrated meaningful benefit in CHF in the outpatient setting;       however release of iron from the liver is likely to be too slow to produce a benefit in hospital      &#8226; Because of the immediate bioavailability of iron, FPC may lead to improved function in a hospitalized patient       (average LOS ~5 days)                                                                           23</FONT></DIV>
